# Layout Patterns

Comprehensive guide to page layout and structure patterns in the @web service.

## Layout Architecture

### Grid-Based Layouts

The application uses CSS Grid for complex layouts:

```tsx
// Resource Layout - Main app layout with header and sidebar
<div className="grid h-screen w-full grid-rows-[auto_1fr] grid-cols-[auto_1fr]">
  <Header className="col-span-2" orgs={orgs} email={email} />
  <div className="h-full overflow-y-auto">
    <UserNavigation />
  </div>
  <div className="pl-2 pb-4 h-full overflow-y-auto">
    <Outlet />
  </div>
</div>

// Admin Layout - Two-tier layout
<div className="grid grid-rows-[auto_1fr] h-screen w-screen grid-cols-[auto_1fr]">
  <div className="col-span-2 bg-red-800 text-white flex justify-center items-center h-10">
    🚧 ADMINISTRATION AREA 🚧
  </div>
  <AdminNavigation />
  <main className="overflow-y-auto">
    <Outlet />
  </main>
</div>
```

### Marketing Layouts

For public-facing pages:

```tsx
// Flexible column layout with header/footer
<div className="flex min-h-screen flex-col bg-white text-gray-900 dark:bg-editframe-900 dark:text-gray-200">
  <Header />
  <main>
    <div className="lg:px-[7.2rem] mx-auto">
      <Outlet />
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</div>
```

## Layout Components

### Header Patterns

#### Application Header
```tsx
interface HeaderProps {
  className?: string;
  orgs: Array<{ id: string; display_name: string }>;
  email: string;
}

export function Header({ className, orgs, email }: HeaderProps) {
  return (
    <header className={clsx("border-b border-gray-200", className)}>
      {/* Header content */}
    </header>
  );
}
```

#### Marketing Header
```tsx
interface MarketingHeaderProps {
  isLoggedIn?: boolean;
  className?: string;
}

export function MarketingHeader({ isLoggedIn, className }: MarketingHeaderProps) {
  const [isScrolled, setIsScrolled] = useState(false);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    function onScroll() {
      setIsScrolled(window.scrollY > 10);
    }
    // Scroll detection logic
  }, []);

  return (
    <header className={clsx(
      "z-1000 w-full transition-all duration-300",
      { "bg-white border-b border-[#E2E2E3]": isScrolled },
      className
    )}>
      {/* Navigation content */}
    </header>
  );
}
```

### Container Patterns

#### Inner Container
```tsx
export function InnerContainer({ children, className }: ContainerProps) {
  return (
    <div className={clsx("mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8", className)}>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

#### Content Container
```tsx
// For docs and content pages
<div className="lg:px-[7.2rem] mx-auto">
  {children}
</div>

// For tools and interactive pages
<div className="lg:px-[5.5rem] max-w-6xl mx-auto">
  {children}
</div>
```

## Responsive Design Patterns

### Breakpoint Strategy
- `sm:` - 640px and up
- `md:` - 768px and up  
- `lg:` - 1024px and up
- `xl:` - 1280px and up

### Mobile-First Layouts
```tsx
// Navigation that collapses on mobile
<nav className="flex space-x-4 text-sm font-medium items-center">
  <div className="hidden md:flex">
    {/* Desktop navigation */}
  </div>
  <div className="md:hidden">
    {/* Mobile menu button */}
  </div>
</nav>
```

### Responsive Grid
```tsx
// Responsive sidebar layout
<div className="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr_auto] overflow-hidden">
  <Menu className="overflow-auto pl-4 pr-8 pb-20" />
  <main className="overflow-auto relative">
    {/* Main content */}
  </main>
  <aside className="hidden lg:block">
    {/* Right sidebar */}
  </aside>
</div>
```

## Overflow Management

### Scrollable Areas
```tsx
// Sidebar with independent scrolling
<div className="h-full overflow-y-auto">
  <UserNavigation />
</div>

// Main content area
<div className="pl-2 pb-4 h-full overflow-y-auto">
  <Outlet />
</div>
```

### Content Containment
```tsx
// Prevent layout shifts
<div className="grid grid-rows-[auto_minmax(0,1fr)] h-screen contain-layout">
  <Header />
  <main className="overflow-hidden">
    {/* Constrained content */}
  </main>
</div>
```

